-- Lucky Cement-Led Group Buys ICI Pakistan for $152.5 Million
-- B y   F a r h a n   S h a r i f
-- 2012-07-30T10:19:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-30/lucky-cement-led-group-buys-ici-pakistan-for-152-5-million.html
A group led by  Lucky Cement Ltd. (LUCK) ,
Pakistan’s biggest maker of the building material, bought 76
percent of chemical producer ICI Pakistan Ltd. from  Akzo Nobel
NV (AKZA)  for $152.5 million, according to a statement to exchanges.  The acquirers, the Yunus Brothers Group, is expanding its
businesses to make soda ash, polyester staple fiber and health
products, Abid Muhammad Ganatra, director of finance at Lucky
Cement, said in a phone interview from Karachi. The group owns
cement and textile makers and power producers.  “We see huge potential for business in ICI with some
improvement and investments,” said Ganatra.  ICI Pakistan rose by its daily limit of 5 percent to 166.06
rupees at close in Karachi. Lucky Cement declined 4.2 percent to
123.85 rupees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Farhan Sharif in Karachi at 
